{"id": "3666", "title": "Bug 3666 - Code Completion: Hungry code assist", "description": "Under certain circumstances, code assist eats too much code. Consider the enclosed class. As a programmer, I must add a parameter to the baz call in bar to make the program correct.", "OB": "The code is changed to: baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me:

baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

public class X {
    void bar(X x) { 
        baz(x.foo()); 
    }
    int foo() { 
        return 5; 
    }
    void baz(int i, int j) { 
    }
}", "EB": "The code is changed to: baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me:

baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

public class X {
    void bar(X x) { 
        baz(x.foo()); 
    }
    int foo() { 
        return 5; 
    }
    void baz(int i, int j) { 
    }
}

The choice between replacing until the end of the current identifier or until the cursor location should be conditioned by a keystroke (enter = replace until end, insert = replace until cursor location).", "SR": "Move the issue to ITPJUI."}
